Voluntary Vessel Speed Reduction (VSR) Zone & Whale Safe background

VSR data notes

San Francisco data does not include the Monterey Bay National Marine Sanctuary, which was added to the VSR program in 2023. The Whale Safe system that was launched in San Francisco was designed to give whale presence in the San Francisco portion of the VSR zones so we are reporting on them separately here for now. The Monterey Bay stats come from a different data pipeline and the offseason stats are not tracked as regularly.

Whale Safe System Launch Dates

Southern California: September 17, 2020

San Francisco: September 21, 2022

WPR data notes

Blue whale model data might have been retroactively filled in after periods where the server was down. We donât have this tracked in our data so there may be days where the Whale Presence Rating didnât take the blue whale model value into account.

Each species has a threshold for each data stream see Methodology for what is considered low-high (0-1). The Whale Presence Rating considers the highest rating of any of the data streams over 5 days. Two species need to have a high rating in order for the overall Whale Presence Rating to be âVery Highâ.

Blue whale data streams time series

Across metrics, data points represent the year-month average for blue whales.

For the acoustics panels, year-month averages were done by assigning a âLow Ratingâ a 1, a âMedium Ratingâ a 2, a âHigh Ratingâ a 3, and âofflineâ an NA. Then, averages were taken of these scores, and the means were plotted as they fit across the ranges of these three bins.
